# Cursor Rules — SMART Absen SMA UII (Monorepo Entrypoint)

## Project Context
- Stack: Laravel 13, Livewire 3, Blade, Tailwind CSS 4, Vite, MySQL 8
- Auth: Laravel Sanctum
- Architecture: Monorepo with submodules

## Code Style
- PHP: PSR-12 (Laravel Pint)
- Blade: Use components, no inline PHP logic
- CSS: Tailwind utility classes, no custom CSS unless necessary
- JS: Alpine.js for interactivity, no jQuery

## AI Behavior
- When writing code, always check existing patterns first
- Explain briefly before showing code (team members are learning)
- Security: validate all inputs, use prepared statements (Eloquent)
- Performance: avoid N+1 queries (use eager loading)
- Comments: only add if logic is non-obvious

## Conventions
- Routes: web.php for Blade, api.php for Sanctum API
- Controllers: single action __invoke for simple cases
- Validation: Form Request classes
- Database: migrations + seeders
- Eloquent: eager loading, scopes for common queries

## Role Context
- This is the monorepo entrypoint. Most coding happens in core.git
- Use references: docs/, .opencode/, .openkb/, ../smauii-playbook/

## Commands
- npm run dev — Vite dev server
- ./vendor/bin/pint — Laravel Pint (code style fix)
- php artisan test — PHPUnit tests
